  "doc_id": "43299",
  "text": "Recently, Tanaka and Asai [19, [CITATION_1] formulated the multiobjective linear programing problems with fuzzy parameters. Following the fuzzy decision or minimum operator proposed by Bellman and Zadeh [I] together with triangular membership functions for fuzzy parameters, they considered two types of fuzzy multiobjective linear programming problems; one is to decide the nonfuzzy solution and the other is to decide the fuzzy solution.",
  "correct_citation": {
